# Terms of Service Agreement Drafting Skill

## Purpose
To assist in drafting clear, compliant Terms of Service Agreements tailored for various platforms and regulated industries.

## Prerequisites
1. Understanding of contract law basics.
2. Familiarity with platform-specific practices.
3. Knowledge of regulatory requirements such as GDPR, CCPA, DMCA.
4. Awareness of applicable jurisdictional laws.
5. Capability to identify business-specific needs and user interactions.

## Sections Overview
- Introduction & Acceptance
- User Obligations & Restrictions
- Intellectual Property Rights
- Privacy & Data Protection
- Liability & Disclaimers
- Termination Clauses
- Governing Law & Dispute Resolution
- Updates & Amendments

## Input Checklist
| Item                          | Required | Notes                             |
|-------------------------------|----------|----------------------------------|
| Platform type                 | Yes      | Website, SaaS, mobile app, etc. |
| Target jurisdiction           | Yes      | Specify for governing law        |
| User demographic              | Optional | Age restrictions (COPPA)         |
| Data collection specifics     | Yes      | To align with privacy clauses    |
| Third-party services usage   | Optional | Include relevant clauses         |
| Regulated industry status     | Yes      | Triggers extra compliance needs  |

## Clause Matrix
| Clause                      | Description                                             | Regulated Industry Concerns                 | Compliance Notes                       |
|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Acceptance of Terms          | User agreement to the terms                             | Must allow clear consent options           | GDPR compliant consent mechanisms    |
| User Obligations            | Usage limits, prohibited activities                     | Enhanced monitoring if regulated           | Must avoid unfair restrictions       |
| Intellectual Property Rights | Ownership and license terms                              | Sensitive if content created by users      | DMCA takedown procedures [VERIFY]   |
| Privacy & Data Protection    | Data collection, usage, storage policies                | Critical section: GDPR, CCPA, ECPA, COPPA  | Data breach notification obligations |
| Limitation of Liability      | Limits platform’s legal exposure                        | Must balance enforceability                  | State-specific caps may apply        |
| Termination                 | Grounds and procedures for ending user access           | Additional criteria if regulated industry  | Notice requirements must be clear    |
| Governing Law & Disputes     | Jurisdiction, arbitration or court options               | Must respect local mandatory laws          | Arbitration clauses [VERIFY]         |
| Updates & Amendments         | How terms can be modified and communicated               | Special rules if affecting regulated users | User notification protocols          |

## Drafting Steps
1. Gather platform and jurisdiction information.
2. Identify regulatory requirements (GDPR, CCPA, DMCA, COPPA, ECPA).
3. Customize user obligations and prohibited activities.
4. Draft clear privacy and data protection clauses with variable placeholders.
5. Include intellectual property terms compatible with user content.
6. Define liability limitations respecting jurisdiction caps.
7. Establish termination conditions aligned with industry norms.
8. Specify governing law and dispute resolution processes.
9. Outline update mechanisms with user notice.
10. Review compliance notes and insert [VERIFY] flags for uncertain points.

## Optional Modules
- COPPA Compliance: Catering to child data privacy with consent mechanisms.
- DMCA Procedures: Takedown and counter-notice processes for copyright enforcement.
- ECPA Considerations: Handling wiretap and electronic communications laws.
- Regulated Industry Addendum: Specific clauses for finance, health, or other sectors.

## Jurisdiction Modules
| Jurisdiction | Notes                                                   |
|--------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| EU           | GDPR focus, data subject rights, breach notifications  |
| US - California | CCPA specific rights, do-not-sell opt-out            |
| US - Federal | COPPA, DMCA, ECPA compliance                             |
| Others       | Adapt governing law and dispute clauses accordingly     |

## Guidelines

### Do
- Use clear, simple language to avoid ambiguity.
- Incorporate explicit consent mechanisms where required.
- Ensure transparency in data handling and user rights.
- Regularly update terms to reflect regulatory changes.
- Tailor clauses to platform specifics and user base.

### Don’t
- Include overly broad liability waivers that may be unenforceable.
- Rely on implied consent for sensitive data processing.
- Neglect jurisdictional nuances in governing law or disputes.
- Overlook regulated industry-specific rules and notifications.

### Compliance Notes
- Ensure GDPR compliance with data subject rights and lawful processing.
- Implement CCPA’s “Do Not Sell” options and privacy notices.
- Incorporate DMCA takedown processes with proper notices.
- Consider COPPA rules if users include children under 13.
- Observe ECPA’s electronic communication protections where applicable.
- [VERIFY] jurisdiction-specific enforcement and recent amendments.

## Variable Placeholders Example
```markdown
- [PlatformName]: The name of the platform.
- [User]: The individual or entity using the service.
- [Jurisdiction]: The applicable legal jurisdiction.
- [ContactEmail]: Compliance contact address.
- [EffectiveDate]: Date the terms become effective.
```

## Template Skeleton
```markdown
# Terms of Service Agreement

## 1. Introduction
Welcome to [PlatformName]. By accessing or using our service, you agree to these Terms as of [EffectiveDate].

## 2. Acceptance of Terms
[User] agrees to comply with the terms outlined herein.

## 3. User Obligations
You shall not engage in prohibited activities including [ListProhibitedActivities].

## 4. Intellectual Property
Content remains property of [PlatformName] or respective owners.

## 5. Privacy and Data Protection
Our privacy practices comply with [Jurisdiction] laws detailed in our Privacy Policy.

## 6. Liability Limitations
[PlatformName]'s liability is limited to [ClauseDetails] as permitted by law.

## 7. Termination
We may suspend or terminate your access for violations per [TerminationCriteria].

## 8. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution
These terms are governed by laws of [Jurisdiction]. Disputes shall resolve via [Method].

## 9. Updates
Terms may be updated with notification sent to [ContactEmail].

## Contact
For questions, contact us at [ContactEmail].
```

## Input Checklist Recap
Ensure all inputs from platform type to data specifics are gathered before drafting.

---

[VERIFY] indicates areas needing confirmation or jurisdiction-specific checks.
